## Destructuring

If you use destructuring with a `$derived` declaration, the resulting variables will all be reactive this...

```js
function stuff() { return { a: 1, b: 2, c: 3 } }
// ---cut---
let { a, b, c } = $derived(stuff());
```

...is roughly equivalent to this:

```js
